# SmartBrain_3000 — environment template.
#
# Copy to "compose/.env" (the only env file Docker Compose loads) if you need to override
# a default below. NEVER commit your real .env — it is git-ignored. Most installs need none.
#
# IMPORTANT: provider API keys (OpenAI/Anthropic/Google) are NOT set here. You enter
# them in the app (Settings -> Cloud providers); they are encrypted at rest and never
# read from the environment. Local models (Ollama/MLX) are configured in the app too.

# Port the app serves on (host + in-container). Default 33000.
# SMARTBRAIN_PORT=33000

# Embedding model for semantic Knowledge search, routed to Ollama via Bifrost. The exact
# tag matters. Keep it LOCAL — a cloud model (e.g. openai/...) sends your KB content
# off-box on every reindex. The installer pulls the default for you.
# SMARTBRAIN_EMBED_MODEL=ollama/nomic-embed-text:v1.5

# LAN/HTTPS and remote access (phone) are configured by the installer, not by hand:
#   python3 installer/install.py certs <name>.local <LAN-IP>   # issues the mkcert TLS cert into data/certs/
#   python3 installer/install.py webrtc up                      # remote access (off by default)
# `webrtc up` persists the SMARTBRAIN_SIGNALING_* (and TURN/ICE) values into compose/.env so remote
# access survives a restart. SMARTBRAIN_TLS_* and SMARTBRAIN_ALLOWED_HOSTS come from the LAN overlay
# (docker-compose.lan.yml) or your own compose/.env — set SMARTBRAIN_ALLOWED_HOSTS yourself for LAN.
# See docs/07-remote-access.md.

# Native Linux only: the app runs as a non-root user (uid 10001) inside the container, so a
# root-owned ./data bind mount can block DB file creation. If the app can't write to data/,
# run once:  sudo chown -R 10001:10001 ./data   (Docker Desktop on macOS/Windows is unaffected).
